vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Apache HTTP Server Version

vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Upgrade to Apache Log4j version 2.16.0 or later since 1.x is end of life.

Upgrading to the latest versions for Apache Log4j is highly recommended as intermediate 
versions / patches have known high severity vulnerabilities and the vendor is updating 
their advisories often as new research and knowledge about the impact of Log4j is 
discovered. Refer to https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/security.html for the latest 
versions.

Multiple solutions exist to resolve this vulnerability :

  - Upgrade to IBM Rational System Architect 11.3.1.4 (eGA
    29 April 2011) / 11.4.0.3 (eGA 29 April 2011) or later.

  - Install Microsoft KB2562937 (Update Rollup for ActiveX
    Kill Bits).

    within Internet Explorer per the IBM advisory.

  - Disable all ActiveX controls in the Internet Zone.

'RestrictAnonymous' registry setting to an appropriate value.

Refer to the 'See also' section for guidance.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows SMB NativeLanManager Remote System Information Disclosure

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows SMB Registry Remotely Accessible
Microsoft Windows SMB Share Hosting Office Files
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Make sure that the files containing confidential information have
proper access controls set on them.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows SMB Share Hosting Possibly Copyrighted Material
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Delete the files infringing copyright.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows SMB Share Permissions Enumeration
Microsoft Windows SMB Shares Access
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
To restrict access under Windows, open Explorer, do a right click on
each share, go to the 'sharing' tab, and click on 'permissions'.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows SMB Shares Enumeration
Microsoft Windows SMB Shares Unprivileged Access
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
To restrict access under Windows, open Explorer, right click on
each share, go to the 'Sharing' tab, and click on 'Permissions'.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows Server 2008 SEoL
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to a version of Microsoft Windows that is currently supported.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows Server 2012 / 2012 R2 ESU Status Check
Microsoft Windows Server 2012 SEoL
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to a version of Microsoft Windows that is currently supported.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows Summary of Missing Patches
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Run Windows Update on the remote host or use a patch management
solution.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows Unquoted Service Path Enumeration
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Ensure that any services that contain a space in the path enclose the
path in quotes.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft Windows Update Reboot Required
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Reboot the remote system to put pending changes into effect.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) and XML Core Services Unsupported
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Upgrade the software packages responsible for the unsupported DLL
versions or upgrade to a supported version of Windows (Vista / 2008 or
later). Alternatively, uninstall the outdated MSXML or XML Core
Services.
Upgrade to MongoDB version 5.0.27 / 6.0.16 / 7.0.12 / 7.3.3 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: NFS Share User Mountable
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Configure NFS on the remote host so that only authorized hosts can
mount the remote shares. The remote NFS server should prevent mount
requests originating from a non-privileged port.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Node.js 18.x < 18.20.4 / 20.x < 20.15.1 / 22.x < 22.4.1 Multiple Vulnerabilities (Monday, July 8, 2024 Security Releases).
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to Node.js version 18.20.4 / 20.15.1 / 22.4.1 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Node.js Module node-tar < 6.2.1 DoS
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to node-tar version 6.2.1 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Non-compliant Strict Transport Security (STS)
OS Security Patch Assessment Failed
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Fix the problem(s) so that OS Security Patch Assessment is possible.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Open Port Re-check
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Steps to resolve this issue include :

- Increase checks_read_timeout and/or reduce max_checks.

- Disable any IPS during the Nessus scan

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: OpenSSL 3.1.0 < 3.1.8 Vulnerability
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to OpenSSL version 3.1.8 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Oracle Database Server (October 2024 CPU)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Apply the appropriate patch according to the October 2024 Oracle Critical Patch Update advisory.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Oracle Document Capture Multiple Vulnerabilities
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
If using Oracle's Document Capture client, apply the patch from Oracle to disable the ActiveX controls.

If using a different application that includes the NCSEcw.dll control, set the kill bit for the affect control as
discussed in Hexagon Geospatial's advisory.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Oracle GlassFish Server Path Traversal
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Contact to vendor for patch options.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Oracle GlassFish Server URL normalization Denial of Service
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Contact to vendor for patch options.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Oracle Java JRE Unsupported Version Detection
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to a version of Oracle Java JRE that is currently supported.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Oracle MySQL Workbench < 8.0.36 (January 2024)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to Oracle MySQL Workbench version 8.0.36 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: PostgreSQL 11.x < 11.11 / 12.x < 12.6 / 13.x < 13.2 Multiple Vulnerabilities
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to PostgreSQL 11.11 / 12.6 / 13.2 or later

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: PuTTY < 0.81 Key Recovery Attack Vulnerability
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to PuTTY version 0.81 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Python Software Foundation Python Installed (Windows)
Remote Desktop Protocol Server Man-in-the-Middle Weakness
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
- Force the use of SSL as a transport layer for this service if
supported, or/and

- On Microsoft Windows operating systems, select the 'Allow connections
only from computers running Remote  Desktop with Network Level
Authentication' setting if it is available.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SMB Signing not required
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Enforce message signing in the host's configuration. On Windows, this
is found in the policy setting 'Microsoft network server: Digitally
sign communications (always)'. On Samba, the setting is called 'server
signing'. See the 'see also' links for further details.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSH Password Authentication Accepted
SSH Protocol Versions Supported
SSH Server Type and Version Information
SSL Certificate Expiry
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Purchase or generate a new SSL certificate to replace the existing
one.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSL Certificate with Wrong Hostname
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Purchase or generate a proper SSL certificate for this service.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSL Cipher Suites Supported
SSL Medium Strength Cipher Suites Supported (SWEET32)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Reconfigure the affected application if possible to avoid use of
medium strength ciphers.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSL RC4 Cipher Suites Supported (Bar Mitzvah)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Reconfigure the affected application, if possible, to avoid use of RC4
ciphers. Consider using TLS 1.2 with AES-GCM suites subject to browser
and web server support.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSL Version 2 and 3 Protocol Detection
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Consult the application's documentation to disable SSL 2.0 and 3.0.
Use TLS 1.2 (with approved cipher suites) or higher instead.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSL Weak Cipher Suites Supported
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Reconfigure the affected application, if possible to avoid the use of
weak ciphers.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSL/TLS Diffie-Hellman Modulus <= 1024 Bits (Logjam)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Reconfigure the service to use a unique Diffie-Hellman moduli of 2048
bits or greater.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: SSLv3 Padding Oracle On Downgraded Legacy Encryption Vulnerability (POODLE)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Disable SSLv3.

Services that must support SSLv3 should enable the TLS Fallback SCSV
mechanism until SSLv3 can be disabled.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Server Message Block (SMB) Protocol Version 1 Enabled
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Disable SMBv1 according to the vendor instructions in Microsoft
KB2696547. Additionally, block SMB directly by blocking TCP port 445
on all network boundary devices. For SMB over the NetBIOS API, block
TCP ports 137 / 139 and UDP ports 137 / 138 on all network boundary
devices.
Upgrade Splunk Universal Forwarder to versions 9.2.1, 9.1.4, and 9.0.9, or higher.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: TLS Version 1.0 Protocol Detection
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Enable support for TLS 1.2 and 1.3, and disable support for TLS 1.0.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: TLS Version 1.1 Deprecated Protocol
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Enable support for TLS 1.2 and/or 1.3, and disable support for TLS 1.1.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Terminal Services Doesn't Use Network Level Authentication (NLA) Only
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Enable Network Level Authentication (NLA) on the remote RDP server. This is
generally done on the 'Remote' tab of the 'System' settings on Windows.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Terminal Services Encryption Level is not FIPS-140 Compliant
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Web Application Cookies Are Expired
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Each cookie should be carefully reviewed to determine if it contains
sensitive data or is relied upon for a security decision.

If needed, set an expiration date in the future so the cookie will
persist or remove the Expires cookie attribute altogether to convert
the cookie to a session cookie.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Web Server No 404 Error Code Check
Web Server Unconfigured - Default Install Page Present
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Disable this service if you do not use it.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Web Server robots.txt Information Disclosure
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Review the contents of the site's robots.txt file, use Robots META tags
instead of entries in the robots.txt file, and/or adjust the web
server's access controls to limit access to sensitive material.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: WinSCP < 6.3.3 Key Recovery Attack Vulnerability
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Upgrade to WinSCP version 6.3.3 or later.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Windows 10 / Windows Server 2016 September 2017 Information Disclosure Vulnerability (CVE-2017-8529)
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Refer to the Microsoft CVE article for additional information.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: Windows Defender Antimalware/Antivirus Signature Definition Check
vulnerability_insights.Solutions: Trigger an update manually and/or enable auto-updates.

vulnerability_insights.Vulnerability Name: web.config File Information Disclosure
vulnerability_insights.Solutions:
Ensure proper restrictions are in place, or remove the web.config
file if the file is not required.

common_critical.Name: MS16-120: Security Update for Microsoft Graphics Component (3192884)
common_critical.Description:
The remote Windows host is missing a security update. It is,
therefore, affected by multiple vulnerabilities :

  - Multiple information disclosure vulnerabilities exist in
    the Windows GDI component due to improper handling of
    objects in memory. A local attacker can exploit these
    vulnerabilities, via a specially crafted application, to
    predict memory offsets in a call stack and bypass the
    Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR) feature,
    resulting in the disclosure of memory contents.
    (CVE-2016-3209, CVE-2016-3262, CVE-2016-3263)

  - An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists in the
    Windows kernel due to improper handling of objects in
    memory. A local attacker can exploit this to elevate
    privileges and execute code in kernel mode.
    (CVE-2016-3270)

  - A remote code execution vulnerability exists in the
    Windows GDI component due to improper handling of
    objects in memory. An unauthenticated, remote attacker
    can exploit this vulnerability by convincing a user to
    visit a specially crafted website or open a specially
    crafted file, resulting in the execution of arbitrary
    code in the context of the current user. (CVE-2016-3393)

  - A remote code execution vulnerability exists in the
    Windows font library due to improper handling of
    embedded fonts. An unauthenticated, remote attacker
    can exploit this vulnerability by convincing a user to
    visit a specially crafted website or open a specially
    crafted document file, resulting in the execution of
    arbitrary code in the context of the current user.
    (CVE-2016-3396)
  
  - An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists in the
    Windows GDI component due to improper handling of
    objects in memory. A local attacker can exploit this to
    elevate privileges and execute code in kernel mode.
    (CVE-2016-7182)

    Remote version : 3.0.6920.8712
    Should be      : 3.0.6920.8720

common_critical.Name: MS16-014: Security Update for Microsoft Windows to Address Remote Code Execution (3134228)
common_critical.Description:
The remote Windows host is missing a security update. It is,
therefore, affected by multiple vulnerabilities :

  - An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists in the
    Windows kernel due to improper handling of objects in
    memory. A local attacker can exploit this, via a crafted
    application, to run arbitrary code in kernel mode and
    therefore take control of the affected system.
    (CVE-2016-0040)

  - Multiple code execution vulnerabilities exist due to
    improper validation of user-supplied input when loading
    DLL files. A local attacker can exploit these, via a
    specially crafted application, to execute arbitrary
    code. (CVE-2016-0041, CVE-2016-0042)

  - A denial of service vulnerability exists in Microsoft
    Sync Framework due to improper processing of crafted
    input that uses the 'change batch' structure. An
    authenticated, remote attacker can exploit this, via
    specially crafted packets sent to the SyncShareSvc
    service, to cause the service to stop responding.
    (CVE-2016-0044)

  - A security feature bypass vulnerability exists when
    Kerberos fails to check the password change of a user
    signing into a workstation. An attacker can exploit
    this, by connecting the workstation to a malicious
    Kerberos Key distribution Center, to bypass Kerberos
    authentication on a target machine, thus allowing
    decryption of drives protected by BitLocker.
    (CVE-2016-0049)
